{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/dweekly/ftr/pulls/3", "id": 2690492241, "node_id": "PR_kwDOO08p1s6gXadR", "html_url": "https://github.com/dweekly/ftr/pull/3", "diff_url": "https://github.com/dweekly/ftr/pull/3.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/dweekly/ftr/pull/3.patch", "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/dweekly/ftr/issues/3", "number": 3, "state": "closed", "locked": false, "title": "v0.2.1: Socket abstraction layer and UDP traceroute improvements", "user": {"login": "dweekly", "id": 444769, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjQ0NDc2OQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/444769?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/dweekly", "html_url": "https://github.com/dweekly", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dweekly/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dweekly/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dweekly/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dweekly/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dweekly/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dweekly/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dweekly/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dweekly/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dweekly/received_events", "type": "User", "user_view_type": "public", "site_admin": false}, "body": "## Summary\nThis release implements a comprehensive socket abstraction layer and fixes critical issues with UDP traceroute on Linux.\n\n## Key Features\n\n### Socket Abstraction Layer\n- Modular socket architecture with factory pattern for automatic mode selection\n- Support for multiple socket types:\n  - Raw ICMP (requires root/CAP_NET_RAW)\n  - DGRAM ICMP (Linux, configurable ping group)\n  - UDP with ICMP reception\n- Automatic fallback between modes based on available permissions\n- Library interface (`lib.rs`) for programmatic use\n\n### UDP Traceroute Improvements\n- **Linux IP_RECVERR support** - UDP traceroute now works without root privileges\n- Fixed UDP traceroute to properly detect all hops using `connect()` + `send()` approach\n- Correctly handles `recvmsg()` edge cases (ret=0 with control messages)\n- One socket per probe design to avoid port collisions\n\n### Multiple Probes per TTL\n- Added `-q`/`--queries` option (default: 1)\n- Send multiple probes to discover all paths in load-balanced networks\n- Matches behavior of traditional traceroute utilities\n\n## Bug Fixes\n- Fixed regression where traceroute continued displaying hops past the destination\n- Socket errors now properly detected using OS error codes instead of string matching\n- Display both hostname and IP address in reverse DNS lookups\n- Removed noisy UDP port 443 notifications\n\n## Infrastructure Improvements\n- Comprehensive test scripts for comparing ftr with system traceroute\n- Enhanced pre-push hooks with mandatory security checks (`cargo audit`)\n- Added file size checks to prevent large file commits (defense against ISOs)\n- Updated documentation for UDP traceroute and multi-mode probing\n\n## Testing\n- Tested on macOS (Darwin) and Linux (Ubuntu 24.04 ARM64)\n- All tests passing\n- Verified UDP works without root on Linux\n- Confirmed ICMP works with appropriate privileges\n- Multiple probes functionality validated\n\n## Breaking Changes\nNone - all changes are backward compatible\n\n\ud83e\udd16 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.ai/code)", "created_at": "2025-07-24T01:45:59Z", "updated_at": "2025-07-24T01:46:21Z", "closed_at": "2025-07-24T01:46:19Z", "merged_at": "2025-07-24T01:46:19Z", "merge_commit_sha": "a625e80a433a2cf99c9ad3c694eb3b8e6f53468d", "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "requested_reviewers": [], "requested_teams": [], "labels": [], "milestone": null, "draft": false, "commits_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/dweekly/ftr/pulls/3/commits", "review_comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/